{
  "texts": [
    "We then compare these with their centralized and vanilla federated versions to assess the recommendation improvements.",
    "Additionally, we compare using solely the LLM server to predict users' preferences without federated sequential recommendation training, to highlight the necessity of training sequential recommendation models.For evaluating empirical privacy protection abilities, we compare FELLAS's perturbation method with random perturbation, where items in user sequences are randomly replaced with other items.",
    "Evaluation ProtocolWe evaluate the model performance using two widely used metrics: Hit Ratio at Rank K (HR@K) and Normalized Discounted Cumulative Gain at Rank K (NDCG@K).",
    "HR measures the ratio of correct items included in the top K recommendation list, while NDCG further evaluates whether the correct items are positioned high on the list.",
    "In this paper, K is set to 10 and 20."
  ]
}